Sir, wait! There could be a bomb.

17
00:02:49,483 --> 00:02:50,716
去他媽的炸彈
Fuck the bomb.

18
00:02:50,718 --> 00:02:52,585
孫子弄壞了我的車
Son of a bitch just ruined my car.

19
00:02:52,587 --> 00:02:54,687
你
You!

20
00:02:54,689 --> 00:02:56,058
從車裏出來
Step out of the van!

21
00:02:58,058 --> 00:03:00,394
手放在我能看見的地方
Hands where I can see them!

22
00:03:02,296 --> 00:03:03,632
趴在地上
On the ground now!

23
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:05,035
一年後

24
00:05:16,831 --> 00:05:19,264
你好 克裏斯蒂·戴維斯
Hi. Christi Davies.

25
00:05:19,266 --> 00:05:21,699
謝謝你的同意 警探
Thank you for agreeing to do this, Detective.

26
00:05:21,701 --> 00:05:24,269
頭兒交辦任務
Well, the way the chief put it,

27
00:05:24,271 --> 00:05:26,504
我沒有太多選擇
I didn't really have much of a choice.

28
00:05:26,506 --> 00:05:30,377
猜我抽了下下籤
Guess I drew the proverbial short straw.

29
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:38,216
你希望獲取什麼?
So, what exactly are you hoping to get here?

30
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:41,586
介於平民和警察
Well, with all the tension between

31
00:05:41,588 --> 00:05:43,956
近期的緊張關係
civilians and police officers lately,

32
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:46,192
我的目標是洞察
my goal is to get some honest insight

33
00:05:46,194 --> 00:05:47,826
在美國的心臟地區
into what it's really like to be a police officer

34
00:05:47,828 --> 00:05:49,928
當警察的真正感覺
in the heart of America.

35
00:05:49,930 --> 00:05:52,769
我不偏袒任何一方 只忠於目標
I'm not here to choose a side, just be true to my subject.

36
00:05:52,966 --> 00:05:54,899
我的家鄉很好 和其他地方一樣
And I figured my hometown was as good a place as any...

37
00:05:54,901 --> 00:05:56,569
聽著
All right, listen. Look.

38
00:05:56,571 --> 00:05:59,234
紙上談兵 說來容易
I'm sure that shit reads great on the page. Okay?

39
00:05:59,259 --> 00:06:02,028
但如果你想開誠佈公 不如你先來
But if you want me to be open with you, you just got to give it to me straight.

40
00:06:03,977 --> 00:06:05,847
我自有理由 警探
I have my reasons, Detective.

41
00:06:11,651 --> 00:06:13,154
你的傷疤是怎麼來的?
How'd you get your scar?

42
00:06:16,256 --> 00:06:18,290
《紐約時報》調查記者
Being a New York Times investigative journalist

43
00:06:18,292 --> 00:06:20,658
並不沽名釣譽
isn't always just awards and accolades.

44
00:06:20,660 --> 00:06:23,795
探究真相
Sometimes finding out the truth...

45
00:06:23,797 --> 00:06:25,300
常有疤痕
leaves scars.

46
00:06:29,770 --> 00:06:31,937
介意我拍攝嗎?
Do you mind if I film you for this portion of the interview?

47
00:06:31,939 --> 00:06:33,335
請隨意
Sure.

48
00:06:44,919 --> 00:06:46,788
你喜歡這份工作嗎 魯內警探?
Do you like your job, Detective Ruiney?

49
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,103
還行吧
Well, it's all right. I guess.

50
00:06:53,909 --> 00:06:55,857
我以前挺喜歡的
I think I used to like it more.

51
00:06:56,864 --> 00:06:58,566
你喜歡你的工作嗎?
You like yours?

52
00:07:00,768 --> 00:07:03,048
我喜歡
Yeah. I do.

53
00:07:05,639 --> 00:07:08,740
自從我離開後 這裏變了很多
Place has changed a lot since I left.

54
00:07:08,742 --> 00:07:10,997
很多變化
Yeah, a lot's changed.

55
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:17,385
曾經全是農場 現在滿是公寓和小區
The place used to be all farms. Now it's condos, development.

56
00:07:18,819 --> 00:07:20,287
那就是美國
That's America.

57
00:07:22,823 --> 00:07:25,293
所有小組 代碼10-54 班克羅夫特小學
All units, 10-54, Bancroft Elementary.

58
00:07:48,049 --> 00:07:49,781
你第一個到現場?
You first on the scene?

59
00:07:49,783 --> 00:07:51,785
對 無人進出
Yeah, no one's come in or out.

60
00:08:10,004 --> 00:08:11,683
呆在這 - 我能...
Stay here. - Can I...

61
00:08:12,372 --> 00:08:14,708
長官 後援正在路上
Sir, backup is on its way.

62
00:08:54,415 --> 00:08:56,483
警察 手伸出來
Police! Show me your hands!

63
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:14,866
是人體模特兒?
Are those mannequins?

64
00:09:16,737 --> 00:09:18,892
你在幹什麼?我差點打中你
What the hell are you doing? I almost shot you.

65
00:09:20,107 --> 00:09:22,975
剛才那個警官繞到後面去了
The officer you left me with went around the back.

66
00:09:22,977 --> 00:09:24,743
所以
So...

67
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,901
我叫你別動的
I told you to stay put.

68
00:09:28,516 --> 00:09:30,883
聽著 你的上司簽字同意的
Listen, your captain signed off on this

69
00:09:30,885 --> 00:09:33,918
我並沒有報名旁觀
and I didn't sign up for this to sit on the sidelines.

70
00:09:34,856 --> 00:09:37,952
很抱歉我進來了
So... I'm sorry, but I'm coming in.

71
00:09:40,694 --> 00:09:41,795
算了
Fine.

72
00:09:53,774 --> 00:09:55,643
劊子手遊戲
Game of Hangman.

73
00:09:59,747 --> 00:10:02,516
兩個傻瓜玩遊戲
Two dummies playing the game.

74
00:10:08,923 --> 00:10:10,925
你的徽章號碼 925
925 is your badge number.

75
00:10:14,227 --> 00:10:16,727
我很擅長數字
I'm good with numbers.

76
00:10:16,729 --> 00:10:17,664
我記得你的
I remember yours.

77
00:10:19,032 --> 00:10:21,668
另一個號碼是誰?
Who's the other number?

78
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:21,158
大多數人退休後都去釣魚 阿徹
You know, most people go fishing in retirement, Archer.

79
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:23,262
是嗎?
Do they?

80
00:11:23,264 --> 00:11:25,810
人們退休後不會去釣魚
People don't go fishing when they retire.

81
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:29,000
他們只會
No. What they do is

82
00:11:29,002 --> 00:11:31,235
四處閒逛 等著
they hang around waiting for their...

83
00:11:31,237 --> 00:11:33,171
收取養老金支票
pension checks to kick in,

84
00:11:33,173 --> 00:11:36,744
然後疑惑 "我這輩子怎麼了?"
and then wonder, "Whatever happened to my life?"

85
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,248
還在做縱橫字謎嗎? - 為什麼不?
Still doing crosswords, huh? - Why not?

86
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:45,116
用拉丁語?
You're doing them in Latin?

87
00:11:45,118 --> 00:11:48,052
對 我做過聖童
Well, yeah. I'm an altar boy.

88
00:11:48,054 --> 00:11:50,721
很早以前 教堂裏學的拉丁語
Way back. That's where I learned my Latin.

89
00:11:50,723 --> 00:11:53,191
曾經是聖童 永遠是聖童?
Once an altar boy, always an altar boy, huh?

90
00:11:53,193 --> 00:11:54,860
真好笑
Oh, that was funny.

91
00:11:54,862 --> 00:11:56,161
從來沒有這樣想過
Never thought of it that way.

92
00:11:56,163 --> 00:11:57,508
你最近怎麼樣?
How have you been?

93
00:11:58,427 --> 00:12:00,032
很好 - 你看起來油光水滑
Good. - You look prosperous.

94
00:12:00,034 --> 00:12:02,100
你也是 夥計
Yeah, you too, man.

95
00:12:02,102 --> 00:12:03,335
你看起來很不錯
You're looking good.

96
00:12:03,337 --> 00:12:05,039
你有保養?
Well... - You working out?

97
00:12:08,107 --> 00:12:09,843
我有保養?
Am I working out?

98
00:12:20,219 --> 00:12:21,991
時光如斯
So this is it, huh?

99
00:12:22,756 --> 00:12:25,190
36年的兇殺案工作後
Thirty-six years working Homicide,

100
00:12:25,192 --> 00:12:29,695
你就在廉價酒吧外 做填字遊戲
and you end up outside a dive bar doing crossword puzzles.

101
00:12:29,697 --> 00:12:32,597
某種程度上讓你心煩?
That upsets you in some way?

102
00:12:32,599 --> 00:12:34,332
我不心煩 - 我對此很滿意
Doesn't upset me. - I'm very happy with it.

103
00:12:34,334 --> 00:12:36,406
我喜歡看世界
You know, I like to watch the world.

104
00:12:37,237 --> 00:12:39,884
因為我從來不睡覺
Because, uh, I never sleep.

105
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:42,095
是
Yeah.

106
00:12:43,410 --> 00:12:44,789
我也一樣
Yeah, me neither.

107
00:12:45,945 --> 00:12:47,141
是嗎?
Yeah?

108
00:12:47,615 --> 00:12:49,981
你想繼續廢話
You want to talk some more about this nonsense

109
00:12:49,983 --> 00:12:52,085
還是開門見山?
or you want to tell me what's on your mind?

110
00:12:54,921 --> 00:12:58,090
維沃小學有一具屍體
There's a body over at Wayward Elementary.

111
00:12:58,092 --> 00:12:59,890
女性 20多歲
Female. Late 20's.

112
00:12:59,892 --> 00:13:01,963
吊著 有個"O"型切口
Hanged with an "O" cut into her.

113
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:07,099
近乎完美的圓圈
Almost perfect circle.

114
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:09,070
很費時間的那種
He took his time doing it.

115
00:13:10,337 --> 00:13:13,337
似乎特意給我們看的
Displaying her. For us.

116
00:13:14,275 --> 00:13:15,442
給我們?
For us?

117
00:13:17,088 --> 00:13:21,379
我們的徽章號碼都刻在了現場的桌上
Both our badge numbers were etched onto a desk at the scene.

118
00:13:22,093 --> 00:13:23,984
不會吧? - 你倒是說說看
Serious? - You tell me.

119
00:13:27,286 --> 00:13:29,654
今天早上會驗屍
Autopsy's this morning.

120
00:13:29,656 --> 00:13:31,923
你過來吧
Why don't you come on down,

121
00:13:31,925 --> 00:13:34,860
看看被害人和犯罪現場的照片
take a peek at the vic, crime scene photos.

122
00:13:35,229 --> 00:13:37,629
你能否找出
See if you can figure out

123
00:13:37,654 --> 00:13:40,358
罪犯想表達什麼
why this perp is calling us out.

124
00:13:44,271 --> 00:13:46,240
你有想法嗎?
Does it remind you of anything?

125
00:13:48,708 --> 00:13:50,207
目前沒有 至少...
I don't think so. At least it...

126
00:13:50,209 --> 00:13:52,747
不眼熟嗎? - 伎倆不同
Doesn't look familiar? - There's a different MO.

127
00:13:56,250 --> 00:13:58,850
甜甜圈店開了
Hey. Donut shop's open.

128
00:13:58,852 --> 00:14:01,286
我請客 - 免費甜甜圈
I'm buying. - Free donuts.

129
00:14:01,288 --> 00:14:03,120
你上次吃過了
You got 'em last time.

130
00:14:03,122 --> 00:14:05,222
那是我一天的欣慰
That's the highlight of my day.

131
00:14:07,727 --> 00:14:09,193
有點習慣了
it took a bit of getting used to.

132
00:14:09,195 --> 00:14:12,330
我是說地方警察局和聯邦調查局不一樣
I mean, local PD is nothing like the FBI.

133
00:14:12,332 --> 00:14:15,332
我以前的同事
Some of my, uh, former colleagues

134
00:14:15,334 --> 00:14:17,402
認為我遷回故里 是瘋了
thought I was crazy to move back here.

135
00:14:18,024 --> 00:14:19,403
他們認為是降級
A demotion in their eyes.

136
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:22,974
但對我來說 一切沒啥兩樣
But, you know, for me it's all the same.

137
00:14:22,976 --> 00:14:25,777
一樣是抓壞人
Still, uh, catching bad guys.

138
00:14:25,779 --> 00:14:26,848
你為什麼回來?
What brought you back?

139
00:14:29,415 --> 00:14:31,187
個人原因
Personal reasons.

140
00:14:33,219 --> 00:14:36,388
我們還是關注工作吧
Look, let's just keep this about the job, okay?

141
00:14:37,627 --> 00:14:40,588
我只是想更好地瞭解你
I'm just trying to get a better sense of who you are.

142
00:14:40,794 --> 00:14:43,798
觀眾喜歡聯繫實際
Audiences really connect with personal stories of their subjects.

143
00:14:45,598 --> 00:14:46,636
肯定的
Yeah, I'm sure they do.

144
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:54,769
沒有信息 -  我打擾你了嗎?
There's no information. - Oh, am I bothering you?

145
00:14:55,074 --> 00:14:56,774
對不起 警官 沒有信息
I'm sorry, sir. There's no information.

146
00:14:56,776 --> 00:14:58,744
有更新就通知我
Well, you just let me know when finding out

147
00:14:58,746 --> 00:15:01,178
我妻子的事是當務之急 混蛋
what happened to my wife is a priority, asshole.

148
00:15:02,742 --> 00:15:04,092
戴維斯小姐
Miss Davies.

149
00:15:05,352 --> 00:15:07,852
我相信那位警探
I trust that my detective

150
00:15:07,854 --> 00:15:09,200
給了你所需要的一切
is giving you everything you need.

151
00:15:09,225 --> 00:15:12,562
對 我們如坐針氈
Oh, yeah. We're, uh, tethered at the hip.

152
00:15:14,194 --> 00:15:16,495
戴維斯小姐 我想提醒你
Miss Davies, I just want to remind you

153
00:15:16,497 --> 00:15:19,669
你看到的屍體曾經是人
that the body that you saw was a person.

154
00:15:20,266 --> 00:15:23,339
有家人 朋友 生活
With a family, friends, a life.

155
00:15:23,407 --> 00:15:26,474
所以我相信你會對之
So I trust that you'll treat anything that you saw

156
00:15:26,906 --> 00:15:28,440
施以絕對的關注
with absolute sensitivity.

157
00:15:28,442 --> 00:15:29,846
肯定的
Definitely.

158
00:15:30,497 --> 00:15:33,255
市長可能已經簽署同意了
And you know, the mayor may have signed off

159
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:36,016
所有的寵物項目 但我沒有
on this all access pet project, but I didn't.

160
00:15:37,483 --> 00:15:40,152
如果你發表
If you print anything

161
00:15:40,154 --> 00:15:43,288
中傷本案本局警探的文章
that compromises the work of my detectives in this case,

162
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:46,023
你會上法庭的
you will find yourself standing in a court of law.

163
00:15:46,025 --> 00:15:48,159
我說得夠清楚嗎?
Do I make myself clear?

164
00:15:48,161 --> 00:15:49,730
是的
Yes.

165
00:15:51,231 --> 00:15:52,364
"是 隊長"
"Yes, Captain."

166
00:15:52,366 --> 00:15:53,965
是 隊長
Yes, Captain.

167
00:15:53,967 --> 00:15:55,621
請原諒
Can you excuse us, please?

168
00:15:55,646 --> 00:15:56,551
謝謝
Thank you.

169
00:15:58,584 --> 00:15:59,792
我跟你說說阿徹
Let me talk to you about Archer.

170
00:16:05,245 --> 00:16:08,379
派克醫生 請到病理科 一號房間
Dr. Parker, please report to pathology, room number one.

171
00:16:08,381 --> 00:16:11,482
你好 有人在家嗎? - 派克醫生
Hello. Anybody home? - Dr. Parker.

172
00:16:13,554 --> 00:16:16,221
大多數人都去釣魚
Uh, you know, most people go fishing.

173
00:16:16,223 --> 00:16:19,124
魯內 以前給我說過此笑話
Oh, you know, Ruiney tried that joke on me earlier.

174
00:16:19,126 --> 00:16:23,327
見鬼 - 現在不好笑了 你好
Ah, damn it. - Didn't work then. Hi.

175
00:16:23,329 --> 00:16:25,462
見到你真好 - 就像以前一樣
So good to see you. - It's just like old times.

176
00:16:25,464 --> 00:16:27,400
我想念你的擁抱
I missed your hugs.

177
00:16:30,304 --> 00:16:31,741
抱歉
Whoa. - Sorry.

178
00:16:31,766 --> 00:16:35,233
記者別在我面前晃
Yeah, get that press pass out of my face.

179
00:16:35,258 --> 00:16:39,188
上次狗仔隊的案子 證據不見了
Last time we had paparazzi on a case, evidence went missing.

180
00:16:39,213 --> 00:16:42,214
先生 我被提名為普利策獎
Sir, I've been nominated for a Pulitzer.

181
00:16:42,216 --> 00:16:44,416
阿徹
Archer. - Yeah.

182
00:16:44,418 --> 00:16:45,386
你認得她?
You recognize her?

183
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,923
不認得
